---
import MainLayout from "../layouts/mainlayout.astro";
---

<MainLayout title="About | Alex Hordal" isHome={false}>
  <div class="page-grid">
    <!-- Left Column -->
    <aside class="page-title-column">
      <h1>About</h1>

      <p class="page-subtitle">
        Bringing over a decade of experience in emergency response and mountain
        operations to cartography and GIS.
      </p>

      <div class="page-section">
        <h2>Background</h2>

        <img
          src="/images/about/biopic.png"
          alt="Alex Hordal and Ukee"
          class="page-image"
        />

        <p>
          My interest in GIS and cartography grew out of years working as a
          first responder in complex operational environments where spatial
          awareness and accurate geographic information can have real
          consequences. Through my experience as an Infantry Officer in the
          Canadian Armed Forces, as a Professional Ski Patroller at Whistler
          Blackcomb, and as a Paid-On-Call Firefighter with the Whistler Fire
          Rescue Service, I developed a strong appreciation for terrain,
          navigation, and the importance of reliable geographic information.
          These roles required teamwork, attention to detail, clear
          communication, and rapid decision-making in dynamic environments where
          terrain, navigation, and situational awareness were critical.
        </p>

        <p>
          During this time, I also began developing
          <a
            href="https://arcg.is/0zL0ie"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer">
            ULLR Maps
          </a>, a terrain-focused mapping project originally created as a
          personal reference tool to better understand the complexity of
          Whistler Blackcomb's terrain. The project eventually grew into a
          public mapping platform and played an important role in my decision to
          pursue cartography and geographic information systems professionally.
        </p>

        <p>
          As I enter the geospatial field, I look forward to applying my
          experience in operational environments to developing maps and
          geospatial tools that help people better understand complex terrain
          and make informed decisions in real-world situations.
        </p>

        <p>
          Download my resume |
          <a
            href="https://arcg.is/0zL0ie"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer">
            Explore my story
          </a>
        </p>
      </div>
    </aside>

    <!-- Right Column -->
    <section class="page-content-column">
      <div class="page-section">
        <h2>Education</h2>

        <div>
          <ul class="mono-list">
            <li>
              <span class="title">
                Diploma, GIS — Cartography &amp; Geovisualization<br />
              </span>

              <span class="institution">
                Centre of Geographic Sciences (COGS), NSCC
              </span>
            </li>

            <li>BA, Geography — Queen's University</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="page-section">
        <h2>Technical Profile</h2>

        <div class="page-subsection">
          <h3>GIS Platforms</h3>

          <ul class="mono-list">
            <li>ArcGIS Pro</li>
            <li>ArcGIS Online</li>
            <li>QGIS</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="page-subsection">
          <h3>Web Mapping & Development</h3>

          <ul class="mono-list">
            <li>ArcGIS Maps SDK for JavaScript (foundational)</li>
            <li>ArcGIS StoryMaps</li>
            <li>Mapbox GL JS (foundational)</li>
            <li>HTML</li>
            <li>CSS</li>
            <li>JavaScript (foundational)</li>
            <li>Mapbox Studio</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="page-subsection">
          <h3>Programming & GIS Automation</h3>

          <ul class="mono-list">
            <li>Python (foundational)</li>
            <li>ArcGIS Pro ModelBuilder (foundational)</li>
           
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="page-subsection">
          <h3>Cartography & Geovisualization</h3>

          <ul class="mono-list">
            <li>Terrain visualization including DEM and topo-bathymetric elevation processing, shaded relief design, and elevation modelling.</li>
            <li>Thematic cartography and spatial data representation</li>
            <li>Cartographic hierarchy, typography, and layout composition</li>
            <li>Colour theory and multivariate symbology design</li>
            <li>Thematic cartography and spatial data representation</li>
            <li>Narrative cartography and data-driven map design</li>
           
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="page-section">
        <h2>Professional Credentials</h2>

        <div class="page-subsection">
          <h3>Emergency Response & Operations</h3>

          <ul class="mono-list">
            <li>Fire Fighter I & II — Justice Institute of British Columbia</li>

            <li>
              Full Service Fire Fighter Operations Program — Justice Institute
              of British Columbia
            </li>

            <li>
              Volunteer Recruit Training — Halifax Regional Fire & Emergency
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </div>
</MainLayout>
